text.tspan: Burden of disease, by age group, World, 1990 to 2019
Disability-Adjusted Life Year (DALYs) from all causes per 100,000 individuals, by age group.
DALYs measure the total burden of disease – both from years of life lost due to premature death and years lived with
a disability. One DALY equals one lost year of healthy life.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019)
